INSERT INTO `articles_mask` (`post`,`native_id`,`post_account_id`,`post_type`) VALUES ("On Tuesdayâ€™s broadcast of CNNâ€™s â€œCuomo Primetime,â€ host Chris Cuomo argued that the planned early July 4 celebration at Mount Rushmore is not an â€œapples to applesâ€ comparison to police brutality protests. Because the protests werenâ€™t organized by official government entities and trying to enforce a mandatory mask rule during the protests, â€œwould have been madness.â€\n Rep. Dusty Johnson (R-SD) stated that the event will be â€œ7,500 folks, in an outdoor venue, with health screening available, everybodyâ€™s going to be given a mask. And you know what, I recommend they wear them. I thought your last segment was very insightful. I think thatâ€™s important. One more thing I want to mention, South Dakota, the landscape in South Dakota is unique. We only have 62 COVID patients hospitalized across the entire state. Our number of cases are going down. This is not Texas. This is not California. This is not Florida. And, frankly, we know that we can do this in South Dakota. Because in the wake of the death of George Floyd, we had protests. We had large numbers of people together in close proximity. They were wearing masks. They were outside. We did not see a spike in infections, and I think celebrating our country is every bit as important as protesting it.â€\n Cuomo then asked why the Mount Rushmore event wouldnâ€™t have social distancing.","1649502048","3","2");
