INSERT INTO `articles_mask` (`post`,`native_id`,`post_account_id`,`post_type`) VALUES ("Cuomo then asked why the Mount Rushmore event wouldnâ€™t have social distancing.\n Johnson responded that masks can cut the transmission rate of coronavirus by over 90%, and encouraged people to wear them.\n Cuomo then asked why mask-wearing wouldnâ€™t be mandatory at the event.\n Johnson said that the people at the National Park Service who are running the event know what theyâ€™re doing.\n Cuomo pushed back that politicians, not the NPS, are making the decision on mask-wearing mandates.","1649502048","3","2");
INSERT INTO `articles_mask` (`post`,`native_id`,`post_account_id`,`post_type`) VALUES ("Cuomo then asked why mask-wearing wouldnâ€™t be mandatory at the event.\n Johnson said that the people at the National Park Service who are running the event know what theyâ€™re doing.\n Cuomo pushed back that politicians, not the NPS, are making the decision on mask-wearing mandates.\n Johnson replied that South Dakota has different circumstances than other states.\n Cuomo then stated that not enough people, â€œespecially at a Trump rally,â€ will wear masks if they arenâ€™t mandated.","1649502048","3","2");
INSERT INTO `articles_mask` (`post`,`native_id`,`post_account_id`,`post_type`) VALUES ("Cuomo pushed back that politicians, not the NPS, are making the decision on mask-wearing mandates.\n Johnson replied that South Dakota has different circumstances than other states.\n Cuomo then stated that not enough people, â€œespecially at a Trump rally,â€ will wear masks if they arenâ€™t mandated.\n Johnson argued that people should wear masks, and that itâ€™s better in the long run to not have government mandates.\n After Cuomo asked again about why there wasnâ€™t a mask mandate for the event, and remarked that not social distancing at the event is â€œdumb.â€ Johnson pushed back by stating, â€œSo, Chris, where was all of this love of mandatory, big government regulations when we had people rightfully exercising their First Amendment rights, in hundreds of communities across the country? Many of them were wearing masks. They should have been. Good for them. But it seems to me that the love of big government only rears its head â€“.â€","1649502048","3","2");
INSERT INTO `articles_mask` (`post`,`native_id`,`post_account_id`,`post_type`) VALUES ("Johnson replied that South Dakota has different circumstances than other states.\n Cuomo then stated that not enough people, â€œespecially at a Trump rally,â€ will wear masks if they arenâ€™t mandated.\n Johnson argued that people should wear masks, and that itâ€™s better in the long run to not have government mandates.\n After Cuomo asked again about why there wasnâ€™t a mask mandate for the event, and remarked that not social distancing at the event is â€œdumb.â€ Johnson pushed back by stating, â€œSo, Chris, where was all of this love of mandatory, big government regulations when we had people rightfully exercising their First Amendment rights, in hundreds of communities across the country? Many of them were wearing masks. They should have been. Good for them. But it seems to me that the love of big government only rears its head â€“.â€\n Cuomo responded that the issue â€œisnâ€™t about big government.â€","1649502048","3","2");
INSERT INTO `articles_mask` (`post`,`native_id`,`post_account_id`,`post_type`) VALUES ("Cuomo then stated that not enough people, â€œespecially at a Trump rally,â€ will wear masks if they arenâ€™t mandated.\n Johnson argued that people should wear masks, and that itâ€™s better in the long run to not have government mandates.\n After Cuomo asked again about why there wasnâ€™t a mask mandate for the event, and remarked that not social distancing at the event is â€œdumb.â€ Johnson pushed back by stating, â€œSo, Chris, where was all of this love of mandatory, big government regulations when we had people rightfully exercising their First Amendment rights, in hundreds of communities across the country? Many of them were wearing masks. They should have been. Good for them. But it seems to me that the love of big government only rears its head â€“.â€\n Cuomo responded that the issue â€œisnâ€™t about big government.â€\n Johnson countered, â€œOK, set aside big government, why would the standard be different for tens of thousands of people out protesting their government, which they have an absolute, First Amendment, right to do, as long as they do it peacefully. Why would you have the rules be different for them, than you would for people celebrating their country?â€","1649502048","3","2");
