INSERT INTO `articles_mask` (`post`,`native_id`,`post_account_id`,`post_type`) VALUES ("Cuomo then asked, â€œFor a protest?â€\n Johnson replied, â€œAbsolutely. You can say, listen, everybody, these are the rules. Youâ€™ve got to follow the rules. But conveniently, CNN and your show werenâ€™t calling for those kinds of regulations.â€\n Cuomo responded, â€œI was talking about super-spreaders with the protests. We had multiple segments about how itâ€™s going to be wrong. But you cannot believe that this is apples to apples. You are organizing this by choice. Those are protests of people who, in many cases, are angry and outraged, and weâ€™re trying to keep the temperature down. We, forget about me, I cover it. You are trying to keep it down. You make the decisions about how the police deal with protesters, on a large scale, and to have them enforce a no-mask policy when theyâ€™re already hitting the streets because of police intervention in their lives would have been madness. Itâ€™s not apples to apples, unless youâ€™re only looking at this through a partisan lens, the left liked the protests, why donâ€™t they like our fireworks display? I think thatâ€™s unfair and counterproductive.â€\n Johnson countered, â€œPolitical convenience is wanting to have an entirely different set of rules for people protesting their country, than for those who are celebrating it. The bottom line is, people should be wearing the masks. And I think a lot of them will be.â€\n Follow IanÂ Hanchett on TwitterÂ @IanHanchett","1649502048","3","2");
