INSERT INTO `articles_mask` (`post`,`native_id`,`post_account_id`,`post_type`) VALUES ("Several of the industryâ€™s biggest TV production houses have extended their shutdowns or again put filming on hold after the Los Angeles County Department of Public Health issued the suggestion that TV and film productions should be put on hold during a rise is coronavirus cases in the area.\n The department recently posted a message on its website saying to, â€œwe ask you to strongly consider pausing work for a few weeks during this catastrophic surge in Covid cases. Identify and delay higher risk activities, and focus on lower-risk work for now, if at all possible.â€\n California has instituted some of the most strict lockdown orders and mask mandates in America. However, according to recent data from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), California is currently inÂ the top three states with the worst coronavirus spread in the United States.\n According to Variety, Warners Bros. has extended the hiatus for productions including Mom, Bob Hearts Abishola, and B Positive.\n Universal TV has decided not to re-start production on series including Mr. Mayor, Kenan, Good Girls, Brooklyn Nine-Nine, Hacks, and Never Have I Ever. However, Brooklyn Nine-Nine, Hacks wasnâ€™t scheduled to go back in front of the cameras until the 18th.","1812922708","3","2");
INSERT INTO `articles_mask` (`post`,`native_id`,`post_account_id`,`post_type`) VALUES ("Fauci repeated his prediction that life could return to normal by fall 2021 but again emphasized that it is largely contingent on â€œefficiently, quickly and effectivelyâ€ rolling out the distribution of the vaccine, as well as â€œa rather strict adherenceâ€ to restrictions and rules, including social distancing and mask-wearing.\n â€œItâ€™s going to take several months. â€¦ Itâ€™s not going to happen in the first few months,â€ he said during a Thursday appearance on MSNBC.\n â€œIf we do it correctly, hopefully, as we get into the end of the summer, the beginning of the fall of 2021, we can start to approach some degree of normality,â€ he said, repeating the prediction made during last weekâ€™s appearance on PODCAST-19.","1812922706","3","2");
INSERT INTO `articles_mask` (`post`,`native_id`,`post_account_id`,`post_type`) VALUES ("Nearly 2.8 million people in the U.S. had been vaccinated as of December 30, according to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.\n â€œWe really need to rethink or think more intensively about how weâ€™re going to reach out and help the states, help the states, and help the local authorities get this job done,â€ he said.\n Last month, the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases director added that other mitigation measures, including universal masking and social distancing, would still be necessary, even after getting vaccinated.\n â€œI would recommend you have an added area of protection,â€ Fauci told CNNâ€™s Jake Tapper in November.\n â€œObviously, with 90 plus percent effective vaccine, you could feel much more confident, but I would recommend to people to not abandon all public health measures just because youâ€™ve been vaccinated,â€ he continued, noting that â€œyou donâ€™t necessarily know for you how effective it is.â€","1812922706","3","2");
INSERT INTO `articles_mask` (`post`,`native_id`,`post_account_id`,`post_type`) VALUES ("â€œIf you work in a restaurant, we have your back. If youâ€™re a hairstylist, we protect your right to earn a living,â€ he said. â€œAnd if you are a parent, we ensure your kids have the right to attend school in person. Lockdowns do not work. School closures have been disastrous yet even today we see across our country businesses shuttered, lives ruined, and schools closed.â€\n Florida, he added, is â€œbetterâ€ for the steps it has taken to reopen.\n DeSantis has remained on the receiving end of criticism from progressives for his handling of the pandemic. Such criticisms began at the start of the pandemic after DeSantisâ€™s initial refusal to eagerly implement lockdown orders. He also refused to issue a statewide mask mandate and began to take significant steps in reopening the state while others remained in lockdown late last year.\n He also came under fire from progressives for prioritizing seniors in the stateâ€™s overall vaccine distribution. CNN went as far as suggesting that the Sunshine State governor was actively â€œbuckingâ€ Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) recommendations by putting the at-risk population first.\n Florida has since vaccinated over one million seniors statewide. Overall, Florida has distributed 2,296,350 vaccinations and administered nearly 2 million, according to the CDCâ€™s January 31 data.","1839480494","3","2");
